section.section:
Each board shall:
Submit to the Secretary an annual report on:
Advise the administrative head of the State residential center on its goals, programs, and policies;
Help in evaluating the degree to which these goals are achieved;
Review and make recommendations about the annual budget of the State residential center;
Assume leadership in developing community understanding of the needs of individuals with an intellectual disability; and
Carry out any other responsibility that the administrative head of the State residential center requests.
